    "name": "memclaw_keystones_set",
    "title": null,
    "description": "Author or remove keystone rules. op: set|delete. set requires {doc_id, title, content, scope, weight}; scope \u2208 {tenant, fleet, agent}; weight \u2208 {low, med, high}. scope=fleet|agent requires fleet_id; scope=agent additionally requires agent_id \u2014 and ``agent_id`` here names the TARGET agent the rule binds to, NOT the caller (caller identity comes from the API key / gateway headers). For scope=tenant and scope=fleet you must OMIT ``agent_id``; passing it returns INVALID_ARGUMENTS. delete requires {doc_id}. Trust gating is dynamic: scope=agent where the TARGET agent_id matches the caller is trust \u2265 1 (self-author); anything else (scope=fleet, scope=tenant, or scope=agent targeting a different agent) is trust \u2265 2.",
